Description: Volunteer worker daemon for the AuspexAI distributed compute network
 The AuspexAI Worker runs on volunteer machines, executes work units
 dispatched by the coordinator, and donates compute to AI safety research.
 .
 Phase 1 lab-grade release: Linux x86_64 + ARM64 only; Ubuntu 24.04+ /
 Debian 12+ supported. macOS / WSL2 packaging arrives in Phase 2.
 .
 Installs a self-contained Python virtualenv at /opt/auspexai-worker/,
 a system-wide systemd user-unit template at /etc/systemd/user/, and an
 AppArmor profile granting the runner subprocess unprivileged
 user-namespace creation (the Phase 2 durable Q-W10 fix). After install,
 each volunteer user runs:
 .
   systemctl --user enable --now auspexai-worker.service
   auspexai-worker login
 .
 to start the daemon and bind their worker to a GitHub identity (T1).
